1
00:00:06,167 --> 00:00:06,967
<i> Are we okay?</i>

2
00:00:07,100 --> 00:00:08,167
<i> What do you want to happen?</i>

3
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:09,767
<i>I just want things to go back
to how they were.</i>

4
00:00:09,900 --> 00:00:11,500
<i>Marj, a lot has really changed.</i>

5
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:14,367
<i>When guys like Paolo and his dad</i>

6
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,133
<i>don't get the attention
they want,</i>

7
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:19,567
<i>that's when they start looking
elsewhere.</i>

8
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:21,100
<i> I have your reward.</i>

9
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:22,233
<i> Where's Paolo?</i>

10
00:00:22,367 --> 00:00:24,167
<i> I think he's upstairs.</i>

11
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:25,033
<i> Love?</i>

12
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:28,500
<i> I wanted to surprise you.</i>

13
00:00:28,633 --> 00:00:30,467
<i>Next time, please let me know
if you're coming over.</i>

14
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,667
<i>What if we'd already finished
here and I was gone?</i>

15
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,567
<i>Then you would've just
wasted your time.</i>

16
00:00:53,267 --> 00:00:54,233
Evelyn.

17
00:00:55,633 --> 00:00:57,100
I'm just going to use
the restroom.

18
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:09,900
Why are you avoiding me?

19
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:13,900
Is it because of what happened
the last time we saw each other?

20
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:19,933
Greg, I don't know
what you're talking about.

21
00:01:21,367 --> 00:01:22,833
Nothing happened between us.

22
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:26,533
So can you just let me through?

23
00:01:26,667 --> 00:01:28,867
I have to pick up Jobert.

24
00:01:29,867 --> 00:01:31,633
You forget pretty fast.

25
00:01:33,467 --> 00:01:35,633
We had a moment, Evelyn.

26
00:01:35,767 --> 00:01:37,233
I felt it.

27
00:01:37,367 --> 00:01:39,900
I know you felt it, too.

28
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:41,333
Stop denying it.

29
00:01:42,533 --> 00:01:43,933
But we can't.

30
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:48,133
We shouldn't.

31
00:01:48,267 --> 00:01:52,233
You're married,
and our kids are married.

32
00:01:54,267 --> 00:01:56,167
They might get the wrong idea.

33
00:01:57,300 --> 00:01:58,333
I know that.

34
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:00,600
Believe me.

35
00:02:02,267 --> 00:02:03,700
I tried to stop it.

36
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,400
I tried to fight it.

37
00:02:07,733 --> 00:02:09,533
But I can't get you
out of my head.

38
00:02:10,867 --> 00:02:13,033
I like how strong you are.

39
00:02:14,433 --> 00:02:15,667
How straightforward you are.

40
00:02:17,033 --> 00:02:19,867
I admire how tough you
are as a single mom.

41
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:26,100
You're different, Evelyn.

42
00:02:27,833 --> 00:02:30,033
You're different
from every woman I've ever met.

43
00:03:26,467 --> 00:03:28,833
You men are all the same!

44
00:03:28,967 --> 00:03:32,133
You're no different
from my first husband.

45
00:03:34,367 --> 00:03:35,667
Do you have any idea...

46
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:41,600
how many times I hoped?

47
00:03:42,133 --> 00:03:43,333
How many times have
I gotten hurt

48
00:03:43,467 --> 00:03:45,700
because he cheated?

49
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:47,433
Because of his mistresses?

50
00:03:48,733 --> 00:03:49,833
And now me...

51
00:03:51,367 --> 00:03:52,500
Me?

52
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,800
You want me
to become your mistress?

53
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:58,300
No.

54
00:03:59,533 --> 00:04:06,933
I don't want any woman to go
through the hell I went through.

55
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:26,667
How is she?

56
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,267
Did anything happen
while I was out?

57
00:04:29,433 --> 00:04:30,900
She threw up, Ma'am.

58
00:04:31,033 --> 00:04:33,200
But I already gave her some ORS.

59
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:37,533
Excuse me, I'll go
prepare her dinner.

60
00:04:38,433 --> 00:04:39,133
- Okay.
- Thank you.

61
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:49,100
How are you, sweetheart?

62
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,000
I'm fine, Mom.

63
00:04:55,167 --> 00:04:56,267
Don't worry.

64
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:59,300
The nurse said throwing up
is normal.

65
00:05:02,733 --> 00:05:05,767
So, what happened
with your trip, Mom?

66
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,500
Did you and Dad make up?

67
00:05:09,367 --> 00:05:11,200
Is everything
back to normal?

68
00:05:14,733 --> 00:05:15,767
Yeah.

69
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,067
Everything's okay.

70
00:05:19,533 --> 00:05:21,133
Don't worry about us.

71
00:05:23,667 --> 00:05:24,767
That's good.

72
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,267
Because, Mom...

73
00:05:29,967 --> 00:05:33,500
I've been worried you and Dad
are fighting because of me.

74
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:40,333
I feel like I'm a burden.

75
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:43,400
Like I caused a rift
between you two.

76
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,933
That's why I'm really
trying to get stronger.

77
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,833
I follow everything
the nurse says.

78
00:05:53,967 --> 00:05:55,733
So you won't fight anymore.

79
00:05:57,233 --> 00:05:59,167
So we can be happy again.

80
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:06,600
Everything will be okay,
sweetheart.

81
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:10,467
Just promise me you'll
get stronger, okay?

82
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,033
So annoying!

83
00:06:35,533 --> 00:06:38,067
I thought I was finally going
to get a taste of Paolo again!

84
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:40,900
Turns out I'd be left hanging.

85
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:26,933
What's so funny?

86
00:07:27,067 --> 00:07:28,533
So loud! Is there a party?

87
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,333
You were talking about me,
weren't you?

88
00:07:34,567 --> 00:07:35,700
Oh no, Ma'am.

89
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:36,767
Of course not, Ma'am Thea.

90
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:39,300
We were just watching
something funny.

91
00:07:40,633 --> 00:07:42,067
Really?

92
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:45,367
Or are you making fun of me?

93
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:49,433
I bet you're gossiping about me,
right?

94
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,300
Having a field day with my life?

95
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,967
Ma'am Thea, no offense.

96
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:00,167
Please don't assume things
about Weng and me.

97
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:03,200
We're just doing
our jobs properly.

98
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:07,833
And besides, what you're
accusing us of isn't true.

99
00:08:07,967 --> 00:08:11,600
We're not the ones doing
anything wrong in this house.

100
00:08:17,933 --> 00:08:19,700
You've got some nerve
talking back to me!

101
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,667
- Ma'am Thea!
- Let go of me!

102
00:08:22,667 --> 00:08:23,700
You're only brave

103
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:26,633
because that goody-two-shoes
Marj is on your side!

104
00:08:26,767 --> 00:08:29,067
But the truth is,
you've got a nasty attitude!

105
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,700
Maybe I should smash your heads
together

106
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:32,533
and knock some sense into you!

107
00:08:33,367 --> 00:08:35,233
- Ma'am Thea, please stop!
- Let me go!

108
00:08:35,367 --> 00:08:36,600
That's enough, Ma'am Thea!

109
00:08:36,733 --> 00:08:39,267
You might kill Cheche!

110
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:46,133
If I ever catch you two
whispering about me again,

111
00:08:46,267 --> 00:08:49,133
I'll cut your tongues out

112
00:08:49,267 --> 00:08:52,233
so you won't have anything
to use for gossiping about me!

113
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,933
You pests!

114
00:09:01,167 --> 00:09:02,700
Are you okay?

115
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:04,833
Does it hurt?

116
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:33,333
Cheche?

117
00:09:33,467 --> 00:09:34,933
What happened?

118
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:36,567
Why are you crying?

119
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:39,400
Ma'am Marj, I just got something
in my eye earlier

120
00:09:39,533 --> 00:09:40,700
from the curtain.

121
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:42,033
Oh no, why?

122
00:09:43,300 --> 00:09:45,067
Why is your neck red?

123
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:47,933
Ma'am, this? It's nothing.

124
00:09:48,067 --> 00:09:51,867
I was just in a hurry
while cleaning up.

125
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,500
I bumped into the corner
of the cabinet.

126
00:09:54,633 --> 00:09:55,933
Don't lie to me.

127
00:09:56,067 --> 00:09:59,067
You don't get marks like that
from bumping into a cabinet.

128
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:03,967
It really was just an accident,
Ma'am.

129
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:08,433
Cheche, look me in the eye.

130
00:10:08,567 --> 00:10:10,367
Tell me the truth.

131
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,033
You don't want me getting mad
at you, right?

132
00:10:12,167 --> 00:10:13,500
Who did this?

133
00:10:16,667 --> 00:10:17,500
Ma'am...

134
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:19,733
Don't be scared.

135
00:10:19,867 --> 00:10:21,033
I'm here.

136
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:23,967
Ma'am...

137
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:26,133
Hey, it's okay.

138
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:36,600
Tell me the truth.

139
00:10:36,733 --> 00:10:39,100
What really happened?

140
00:10:39,233 --> 00:10:42,000
Who's hurting you in this house?

141
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:47,467
What?

142
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,933
Me? Apologize?

143
00:10:49,067 --> 00:10:52,067
Why would I apologize
to a mere maid?

144
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,300
We pay her to follow orders,

145
00:10:54,433 --> 00:10:57,133
not to beg you for help
and run to you.

146
00:10:57,267 --> 00:10:58,300
Just because she's a maid

147
00:10:58,433 --> 00:11:01,433
doesn't mean you can treat her
badly.

148
00:11:01,567 --> 00:11:02,867
She's a person.

149
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,733
And I won't let you walk all
over the people in this house.

150
00:11:06,867 --> 00:11:09,400
If you don't apologize
to Cheche,

151
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:12,367
I'm taking her
to the police station.

152
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:14,600
We'll get a medico-legal report.

153
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:16,900
Do you want me to file
a blotter?

154
00:11:17,033 --> 00:11:20,933
Do you want Dad to find out
how awful you really are?

155
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,633
Fine.

156
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:27,433
I'm sorry.

157
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:29,700
There.

158
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:31,167
Happy now?

159
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:33,667
Try saying it properly.

160
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:37,300
I'm sorry, Cheche.

161
00:11:38,367 --> 00:11:40,133
I just lost my temper.

162
00:11:40,267 --> 00:11:43,167
I promise it won't happen again.

163
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:52,067
If she doesn't keep her promise,
we'll report her.

164
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:01,567
Fine.

165
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:03,733
Play the hero, Marj.

166
00:12:03,867 --> 00:12:05,567
You win this round.

167
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:07,133
But I'll get even.

168
00:12:08,033 --> 00:12:10,467
I'll keep going
after your husband.

169
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:13,967
I'll make him crazy about me

170
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:16,367
until your marriage completely
falls apart.

171
00:12:36,633 --> 00:12:38,733
Hi, Uncle Greg!

172
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:42,367
Hannah, why are you with Jobert?

173
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:44,767
Where's Evelyn?

174
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,400
Mom's not around.

175
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,333
Yes, Sir.

176
00:12:49,467 --> 00:12:52,467
Auntie asked me to take him
home,

177
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:55,000
so we could save on fare.

178
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:56,200
Oh, I see.

179
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:58,100
Smart move.

180
00:12:58,233 --> 00:12:59,633
All right, Sir. We'll go ahead.

181
00:12:59,767 --> 00:13:00,533
Okay.

182
00:13:00,667 --> 00:13:01,900
Bye, Uncle Greg.

183
00:13:02,033 --> 00:13:03,267
Okay. Be safe, Jobert.

184
00:13:08,133 --> 00:13:11,267
<i>You think you're being smart
by avoiding me, Evelyn.</i>

185
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:15,833
<i>It just makes me want
to chase you even more.</i>

186
00:13:26,433 --> 00:13:28,033
So...

187
00:13:28,167 --> 00:13:32,600
when do we continue the
shower we didn't finish?

188
00:13:32,733 --> 00:13:35,667
Thea, please, can you just
sit down for a second?

189
00:13:39,067 --> 00:13:40,233
What's wrong?

190
00:13:41,033 --> 00:13:43,700
We need to lie low
for a few days, Thea.

191
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:48,133
We almost got caught
by Marj last time.

192
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:51,133
I don't want her
getting suspicious

193
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,733
or figuring us out.

194
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:56,033
What?

195
00:13:57,267 --> 00:13:59,400
I was already left
hanging last time.

196
00:13:59,533 --> 00:14:01,967
And now you want
to avoid me, too?

197
00:14:05,867 --> 00:14:07,533
I miss your kisses...

198
00:14:08,567 --> 00:14:10,000
your hugs.

199
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:13,700
You have no idea
how much I crave you.

200
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:20,667
All right, all right.

201
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:24,800
I'll book a hotel this Friday
so it's safer.

202
00:14:25,533 --> 00:14:26,567
No more surprises.

203
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,767
Oh, yes, Paolo.

204
00:14:29,933 --> 00:14:31,000
I can't wait!

205
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:41,800
Sweetie, how are you feeling?

206
00:14:41,933 --> 00:14:45,067
Do you feel nauseous? Dizzy?

207
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,467
Just sleepy, Mom, but I'm good.

208
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:48,433
Okay.

209
00:14:48,567 --> 00:14:50,400
All right, go ahead
and get some sleep.

210
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:54,567
Yolly, Weng, can you
stay with Jas for now?

211
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:55,767
Go ahead, Nurse.

212
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:14,967
Where's Paolo?

213
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:16,400
Why isn't he with you?

214
00:15:16,533 --> 00:15:17,533
Hi, Dad.

215
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:18,800
He's at the office.

216
00:15:18,933 --> 00:15:20,300
He has to work.

217
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:23,800
He needs to work
over the weekend.

218
00:15:23,933 --> 00:15:26,000
I'm so sorry, Marj.

219
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:29,700
I can see that Paolo's work
is affecting your relationship.

220
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:35,600
Honestly, I feel bad for you.

221
00:15:37,733 --> 00:15:39,467
You need all the help
you can get.

222
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:46,033
But Paolo can't just leave
his job, the company,

223
00:15:46,167 --> 00:15:49,967
because we're in the
middle of a crisis.

224
00:15:50,100 --> 00:15:51,800
I understand, Dad.

225
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:55,567
That's why I'm doing everything
I can to take care of Jasmine.

226
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:04,900
Why don't you bring Evelyn
and Jobert back here?

227
00:16:05,033 --> 00:16:08,067
So you'll have help taking
care of my granddaughter.

228
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:12,533
Things will be easier
if you have a support system.

229
00:16:14,867 --> 00:16:16,167
Would that be okay with you?

230
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:18,800
Of course!

231
00:16:18,933 --> 00:16:20,300
It's for my granddaughter.

232
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:24,900
Thank you so much, Dad.

233
00:16:25,033 --> 00:16:26,733
This really helps me a lot.

234
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:30,600
I'll call them
and let them know.

235
00:16:30,733 --> 00:16:31,400
Thank you.

236
00:16:31,533 --> 00:16:32,567
All right, Marj.

237
00:16:43,667 --> 00:16:45,067
What, Marj?

238
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,233
Was it Greg?

239
00:16:46,933 --> 00:16:49,233
Was it Greg who suggested this
to you?

240
00:16:50,067 --> 00:16:51,200
Yes, Mom.

241
00:16:51,667 --> 00:16:53,633
For Jasmine's well-being.

242
00:16:55,633 --> 00:16:56,600
But, Marj...

243
00:16:58,167 --> 00:17:01,867
What if instead of helping,

244
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:05,767
Jobert and I just end up
being a burden to you?

245
00:17:07,233 --> 00:17:12,333
Marj, you know Regina
is really mad at me.

246
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:15,400
There might be issues.

247
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:18,033
It might just make things worse
for you.

248
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:21,667
I understand, mom.

249
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:23,867
But...

250
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:26,333
I'm sorry.

251
00:17:26,467 --> 00:17:28,133
I just want to try.

252
00:17:29,667 --> 00:17:34,700
My child is sick,
and Paolo and I are not okay.

253
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:37,967
I just feel so alone.

254
00:17:44,267 --> 00:17:45,433
Sis...

255
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:51,733
Mom, please just say yes.

256
00:17:51,867 --> 00:17:53,400
Please.

257
00:17:54,100 --> 00:18:00,500
I want to see Baby Jasmine,
so I can take care of her.

258
00:18:00,633 --> 00:18:03,500
So my sister won't cry anymore.

259
00:18:17,633 --> 00:18:19,200
Oscar, get the car ready.

260
00:18:19,333 --> 00:18:21,200
We're going somewhere, okay?

261
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:22,333
Okay.

262
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,033
- Sir.
- Here.

263
00:18:30,167 --> 00:18:30,933
Just put it in the car.

264
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:32,233
Yes, Sir.
I'll just get the vehicle.

265
00:18:32,367 --> 00:18:33,233
All right.

266
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:43,133
Love?

267
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:44,967
Love?

268
00:18:47,567 --> 00:18:48,400
You're leaving?

269
00:18:48,533 --> 00:18:50,400
Jas might look for you.

270
00:18:50,533 --> 00:18:53,533
She's resting now,
and Nurse Daisy's there.

271
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:56,000
I'm going to pick up
Mom and Jobert.

272
00:18:56,167 --> 00:18:59,767
Dad said they can stay here
in the meantime.

273
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:01,600
So I'll have help
taking care of Jas.

274
00:19:01,733 --> 00:19:03,367
Oh, that's good.

275
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:04,833
At least it'll be easier
for you.

276
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,000
Where are you going?

277
00:19:12,967 --> 00:19:14,100
I'm going to the gym.

278
00:19:14,233 --> 00:19:16,500
Just going to work up a sweat,
relieve some stress.

279
00:19:19,067 --> 00:19:22,533
Love, can you come with me?

280
00:19:23,533 --> 00:19:24,333
Please?

281
00:19:24,467 --> 00:19:26,133
Let's pick up Mom and Jobert
together.

282
00:19:29,567 --> 00:19:30,567
Sure.

283
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:32,000
No problem.

284
00:19:32,133 --> 00:19:33,467
Thank you.

285
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,967
I'm going to see Baby Jasmine!

286
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:52,167
Thank you, Good Brother!

287
00:19:52,300 --> 00:19:53,633
Baby Jasmine misses you a lot,
too.

288
00:19:53,767 --> 00:19:56,133
- Come on in.
- I'll go in with Pong.

289
00:19:56,267 --> 00:19:57,300
Careful.

290
00:20:18,933 --> 00:20:20,367
Hello?

291
00:20:21,067 --> 00:20:22,733
Where are you?

292
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:24,100
Let's take a rain check.

293
00:20:26,333 --> 00:20:27,400
What?

294
00:20:27,533 --> 00:20:28,900
But I'm already here!

295
00:20:29,033 --> 00:20:31,867
I even made an excuse to Edward
that I'm staying overnight

296
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,967
at a friend's house.

297
00:20:34,100 --> 00:20:36,000
I'm with Marj.

298
00:20:36,167 --> 00:20:38,767
<i> Go on, just enjoy the hotel.</i>

299
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:41,667
But Paolo, what about me?

300
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:42,900
<i>You're the one
who scheduled this!</i>

301
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:44,067
<i> You should be here!</i>

302
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:47,967
Manang Yolly, can you check
on Jasmine?

303
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:49,967
See if she's asleep already?

304
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:51,800
She's not allowed
to stay up late.

305
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:52,800
No.

306
00:20:52,933 --> 00:20:54,467
I don't have any responsibility
to you.

307
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,033
To my wife, I do.

308
00:20:56,167 --> 00:20:58,900
I'm just waiting for the rest
of Mom's things.

309
00:20:59,033 --> 00:21:00,033
Thank you.

310
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:04,433
Just enjoy the hotel.

311
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:20,867
Love?

312
00:21:22,533 --> 00:21:23,500
Who were you talking to?

313
00:21:23,633 --> 00:21:24,800
Is something wrong?

314
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:32,300
Oh, it's just Manang Yolly.

315
00:21:32,433 --> 00:21:33,700
She's being a bit persistent.

316
00:21:33,833 --> 00:21:35,633
What?

317
00:21:35,767 --> 00:21:39,067
I just got off the phone
with Manang Yolly.

318
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,867
You sure?

319
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,467
Oh, not Manang Yolly.

320
00:21:42,633 --> 00:21:43,500
I mean, Weng.

321
00:21:43,633 --> 00:21:45,333
Weng was the one I was talking
to earlier.

322
00:21:45,467 --> 00:21:47,300
Then she handed the phone
to Manang Yolly.

323
00:21:47,433 --> 00:21:49,900
Probably after you two talked.

324
00:21:50,033 --> 00:21:51,467
She's the only one
whose number I have.

325
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:52,567
I asked her to check

326
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:54,200
if the guest room is ready
for Mom and Jobert.

327
00:21:54,333 --> 00:21:56,267
Of course, I don't want us
to be embarrassed, right?

328
00:21:59,100 --> 00:22:00,900
You don't believe me?

329
00:22:01,033 --> 00:22:03,067
Here, check my call log.

330
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:05,133
See who I called last

331
00:22:05,267 --> 00:22:07,300
so you'll know I'm telling
the truth.

332
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:08,533
Go ahead, Marj.

333
00:22:09,867 --> 00:22:10,767
Go ahead.

334
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:23,233
I'm just curious.

335
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:29,300
I'll go check on Mom.

336
00:22:29,433 --> 00:22:31,067
She's been in the bathroom
for a while.

337
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,100
Okay.

338
00:22:33,767 --> 00:22:35,067
I'll go back.

339
00:22:48,467 --> 00:22:49,900
Cheche.

340
00:22:50,033 --> 00:22:50,933
- Yes, Manang?
- Cheche.

341
00:22:52,533 --> 00:22:53,467
Oh no, Manang!

342
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:55,200
I'll handle that!

343
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:56,767
Oh, Manang.

344
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:58,500
You really need
to be more careful.

345
00:22:58,633 --> 00:22:59,733
I'm sorry.

346
00:22:59,867 --> 00:23:02,100
I didn't mean to.

347
00:23:02,233 --> 00:23:05,233
Well, Manang,
it's your eyesight...

348
00:23:05,367 --> 00:23:06,267
My gosh, Manang.

349
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:08,333
I'm really worried about you.

350
00:23:08,467 --> 00:23:12,033
What if our employers find out
your vision's getting blurry?

351
00:23:12,167 --> 00:23:13,933
They might kick you
out of the mansion.

352
00:23:15,300 --> 00:23:16,467
Oh, Manang.

353
00:23:24,833 --> 00:23:29,133
<i> If Marj asks, tell her
we talked on the phone earlier.</i>

354
00:23:33,733 --> 00:23:35,200
Cheche.

355
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:36,200
Yes, Manang.

356
00:23:38,733 --> 00:23:42,300
They can't just throw me
out of here.

357
00:23:42,433 --> 00:23:45,700
Because I know a lot of
this family's secrets.

358
00:23:49,133 --> 00:23:50,100
Give me that.

359
00:24:11,267 --> 00:24:14,400
Weng, make me some jasmine tea.

360
00:24:14,533 --> 00:24:16,533
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Hi, Ma'am.

361
00:24:16,667 --> 00:24:17,700
Hi.

362
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:20,200
Rose, make Ma'am Regina
some jasmine tea.

363
00:24:20,333 --> 00:24:21,300
Hurry up.

364
00:24:23,833 --> 00:24:28,000
Cath, Rose, Salve.

365
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:29,333
Weng?

366
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:30,700
- Ma'am?
- Are we having some kind of

367
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:31,767
feeding program?

368
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:35,900
Well, Ma'am Marj had all this
food prepared.

369
00:24:36,033 --> 00:24:38,167
Her family's arriving.

370
00:24:38,300 --> 00:24:41,467
And her mom and sibling
will be staying here

371
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:43,533
at the mansion, too.

372
00:24:43,667 --> 00:24:44,533
What?

373
00:24:58,067 --> 00:24:59,033
Come in.

374
00:24:59,167 --> 00:25:00,700
Mommy Evelyn, Jobert, come in.

375
00:25:00,833 --> 00:25:02,200
- Come in.
- Hi!

376
00:25:02,367 --> 00:25:04,533
- Manang Yolly!
- Jobert!

377
00:25:04,667 --> 00:25:07,467
- Weng.
- Welcome back.

378
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:08,967
Please, make yourselves at home.

379
00:25:09,100 --> 00:25:10,333
Oh, hello.

380
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:12,200
You're here.

381
00:25:12,333 --> 00:25:13,500
- Hi, son.
- Mom.

382
00:25:16,367 --> 00:25:18,067
- Welcome back home.
- Come in. Come in, Jobert.

383
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:19,233
Come on.

384
00:25:19,367 --> 00:25:20,033
Marj.

385
00:25:21,967 --> 00:25:23,400
Goodness, is that all
you brought?

386
00:25:24,633 --> 00:25:26,367
Well, I guess it is easier
to move

387
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:28,400
when you don't have that
many things.

388
00:25:28,533 --> 00:25:30,433
Like they say...

389
00:25:30,567 --> 00:25:33,000
less baggage. Literally.

390
00:25:33,133 --> 00:25:36,000
Mom, please.

391
00:25:36,167 --> 00:25:38,200
Let's just make them
feel welcome.

392
00:25:38,333 --> 00:25:39,367
This is for Jasmine.

393
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:42,033
It's for the best.

394
00:25:42,167 --> 00:25:43,133
Yeah, of course.

395
00:25:43,267 --> 00:25:46,100
Oscar, take their things
to the guest room, okay?

396
00:25:46,233 --> 00:25:47,400
The one near the laundry area.

397
00:25:47,533 --> 00:25:49,433
I think they'll feel more
at home there

398
00:25:49,567 --> 00:25:52,033
since the furniture's
not too fancy.

399
00:25:52,167 --> 00:25:53,733
At least it won't be too
intimidating for people

400
00:25:53,867 --> 00:25:56,900
who are used to a simple life.

401
00:25:57,033 --> 00:25:58,267
Oh, and don't worry, Evelyn,

402
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:01,267
I'll have the maids show you
the proper exits

403
00:26:01,400 --> 00:26:03,433
just in case you feel
out of place.

404
00:26:05,367 --> 00:26:09,500
Marj, it kind of feels like
we're not really welcome here.

405
00:26:11,367 --> 00:26:16,267
It feels like everything
we do is wrong.

406
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:22,733
Maybe it's better if we don't
force ourselves to stay here.

407
00:26:22,867 --> 00:26:24,100
We'll just leave, Marj.

408
00:26:24,233 --> 00:26:25,500
- Mom.
- Mom, wait.

409
00:26:25,633 --> 00:26:27,067
Just a second.

410
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:28,833
Let's talk about this first,
okay?

411
00:26:41,233 --> 00:26:42,767
By the way, Paolo...

412
00:26:42,933 --> 00:26:45,767
Your client was waiting
for you at the hotel earlier.

413
00:26:45,900 --> 00:26:48,067
Paolo suddenly canceled.

414
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:49,633
The client was pretty upset

415
00:26:49,767 --> 00:26:52,667
because he was expecting Paolo
to show up.

416
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:55,000
But you said you were
going to the gym.

417
00:26:55,133 --> 00:26:57,333
I thought you were staying
overnight at Lalaine's?

418
00:26:57,467 --> 00:26:58,967
I didn't join them anymore.

419
00:26:59,100 --> 00:27:00,267
I just worked overtime
at the office

420
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:02,300
to fix the company's problem.

421
00:27:02,433 --> 00:27:04,767
Really? Or are you the one
fixing the problems

422
00:27:04,900 --> 00:27:05,800
Paolo created?
